{
  "texts": [
    "Each additional point of the log ratio score signifies a doubling of the disparity between the two corpora for the considered n-gram.",
    "In case of the absence of a term, a tiny value (0.00000000000000000001) was considered instead.",
    "To provide the normalized rate difference of an n-gram in case of its absence in one of the compared corpora, we report the difference coefficient (DiffC), calculated as [33,42]:Difference Coefficient = 𝑁 𝐹 𝑤,𝑇 -𝑁 𝐹 𝑤,𝑅 𝑁 𝐹 𝑤,𝑇 + 𝑁 𝐹 𝑤,𝑅The difference coefficient ranges between +1 (if an n-gram appears only in the target corpus) and -1 (if an n-gram appears only in the reference corpus).",
    "A DiffC of 0 indicates no difference in the normalized frequencies of an n-gram in the compared corpora.",
    "Keyness analysis on corpora from the same field but different points in time can shed light on shifts in language and terminology usage."
  ]
}